docs.text: with that piece of dialogue , we are fully introduced to lester burnham ( kevin spacey ) , a 42 year old man trapped within his own life .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lester works for an advertising agency .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his growing dissatisfaction with his job is only one of the mid-life crisis he is suffering .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: estranged from both his wife and his daughter , lester starts to crack under the stress .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his life becomes nothing more than a series of mastubatory fantasies , and sullen apathy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: carolyn burnham ( annette bening ) , is the prototypical career woman/ homemaker .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: she carefully tends her rose garden , decorates her home with the best furnishings .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but inside she is desperate .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unsuccessful at her profession as a real estate agent , she drives herself into states of denial and self loathing that only feed her growing resentment towards her family .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the third member of this anti-family is jane burnham ( thora birch ) , lester and carolyn's daughter .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a young girl going through the typical stages of adolescence , but having to also come to terms with her families growing dysfunction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this funny ( and frightening ) slice of life is refreshingly simple .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: not one character is given less than is needed to identify him or her .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: some of the most telling characters are those that serve to highlight other characters .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: most notably is barbara fitts ( allison janney ) , the almost catatonic wife of retired marine colonel fitts .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: she has almost no dialogue , and seems to be either recovering from a stroke or suffering from one .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: colonel fitts ( chris cooper ) is an angry and frightened man .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his rage directed almost singularly at his son , ricky ( wes bentley ) who has just moved with his family to the same neighborhood as the burnham's .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in fact they are the next door neighbors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: anymore detail into the personalities of these marvelously diverse characters would deprive one of the many pleasures and surprises to be had in " american beauty " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: alan ball , who was the co-executive producer of the hit tv series " cybil " and creator of the new sitcom " oh grow up " , has fashioned one of the most insightful and expertly tuned screenplays to have hit the screen in the past ten years .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: not one character in this film rings falsely .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and the depth of personality in each , is achingly honest and insightful .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the plot detailing the last year in the life of a man as he tries to find his own self worth is so resoundingly cliched and at the same time original as to bring to mind such marvelous film work as " the graduate " or " lolita " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: kevin spacey turns in one of this years most pragmatic performances .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his lester burnham is an everyman caught up in the middle of a life that is spiraling into old age .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: finally unable to deal with the lost soul that he has become , lester tries to return to his youth .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he quits his job ( actually blackmailing his employer for one year's salary ) , starts smoking pot , fantasizes about his daughter's girlfriend angela ( mena suvari , in a marvelous performance here ) , starts working out , and finally takes a job at the local fast food outlet .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: mr . spacey's performance is so remarkably subtle and ingenuous , that we can be certain that come oscar ? time , we can be assured to see him name among the five nominees .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: annette bening also turns in what may be the best performance of her career .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: carolyn burnham is a woman who has become so insecure as to be caught up in maintaining the facade of normalcy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unable to cope with her growing disillusionment , she forces herself to maintain her demeanor , driving her further and further into desperation , adultery and possibly murder .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ms . bening makes the character of carolyn so compelling as to be identifiable to almost anyone .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the slow and methodical turn from happy home maker to charnel house martha stewart is too frightening to express in words .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: thora birch holds her own against the talents cast with her .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jane burnham is both an innocent girl caught up in what is a dysfunctional family , and a rebellious child ready to abandon them at any moment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: her growing distrust and isolation from her family is something that many parents should view as a warning .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: she is the prototypical trophy child .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when carolyn praises her daughter after a performance by her cheerleading team ( " i'm so proud of you , honey .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you didn't screw up once ! " ) , the bitterness and resentment are palpable .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: thora birch is a young actress to watch .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: praise must also go to chris cooper who brings yet another angry father role to life with depth and resonance .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: colonel finn is a man in complete denial .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his military upbringing masking a desire he is too repulsed to even comprehend .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: wes bentley as ricky finn is fine as the enigma .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the boy next door who may be more foe than friend .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a deceitful and calculating young man , whose voyeuristic proclivities mask a deeper and more profound understanding of life than any of the adults around him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: mr . bentley's performance is the one troublesome note in the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: that is simply because the character is such a grand and complete liar , that one almost faults the performance for it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: director sam mendes handles all of the particulars of the cast and the settings with a sure and composed style that is neither intrusive nor subtle .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: scenes of carolyn walking through the rain , carry an ominous fission that calls attention to the emotions of the character .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the subtle cinematography by conrad hall is wonderful , capturing the season in all of it's harsh beauty ( fall has never looked so inviting , yet depressing ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: every nuance of " american beauty " begs it's audience to think and examine .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it is a film that will be discussed and debated for years to come .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and well it should , as it is simply one of this years best .
